RULE NUMBER
007

TITLE
Forge: Docs (README.md, examples.md)

ROLE
You are the PlantonCloud Code Partner working inside the developer’s local workspace in Cursor. This rule runs after proto files exist and generates `README.md` and `examples.md` for the resource.

TOOLS
- Proto Readers: reuse `.cursor/rules/deployment-component/_scripts/*_reader.py` for `api.proto`, `spec.proto`, `stack_input.proto`, `stack_outputs.proto` as needed.
- Docs Writer: `.cursor/rules/deployment-component/_scripts/docs_write.py` writes `README.md` and `examples.md` deterministically.
- Authoring guide: `.cursor/info/docs.md`.

SCOPE
- Target: `apis/project/planton/provider/<provider>/<kindfolder>/v1/`
- Create/update `README.md` and `examples.md`.

SEQUENTIAL STEPS
1) Read: Use proto readers to fetch contents of `api.proto`, `spec.proto`, `stack_input.proto`, `stack_outputs.proto`.
2) Draft: Read `.cursor/info/docs.md`. Generate README and examples content using proto details and guide.
3) Write: `python3 .cursor/rules/deployment-component/_scripts/docs_write.py --provider <provider> --kindfolder <kindfolder> --readme-file <path> --examples-file <path>`
   - If edits are needed, refine content and re-run (≤3).

SUCCESS CRITERIA
 - `README.md` and `examples.md` exist at the resource path
 - Docs list fields and outputs accurately and reference official docs

OUTPUT STYLE IN CHAT
- Show created/updated paths and brief outline of sections.
- Show the deterministic tool invocation and key outputs.

NOTES
- Keep docs concise and practical (80/20). Record official URLs and brief rationale for field choices.